Which section are you trying to waitlist for? Are you sure that there's space on the waitlist for your section?

See https://eecs.berkeley.edu/resources/undergrads/cs/degree-reqs/enrollment-policy#lower for enrollment policy for 61B.

Which section are you trying to waitlist for? Are you sure that there's space on the waitlist for your section?

See https://eecs.berkeley.edu/resources/undergrads/cs/degree-reqs/enrollment-policy#lower for enrollment policy for 61B.

In addition to Steven's answer, please be sure to actually view the enrollment data by clicking on the class through schedule.berkeley.edu or classes.berkeley.edu.  Seeing a green circle is not sufficient to ensure the class has space.

Also, for 61B, if you are receiving a request for a permission #, you are trying to enroll for a lab and/or discussion that are set aside for the cs scholars program (identified as such in notes on the schedule of classes). Try other sections and you should be able to at least waitlist and perhaps directly enroll.

I get the following error when trying to add myself to the waitlist for CS 189.

Request not processed. There is no wait list available. The wait list request was not processed, as there are no wait list places available for one or more of the class sections in this request.

There are definitely still spots available on the waitlist, so why is this happening? Also, as an upper-division, non-cs major how can I add 61B? I am getting a permission error when I try to enroll in the class.
